Class `c1` is `public`, therefore `c4` from another package has access to it. But, variable `c1.a` is `protected`, it means that it&#39;s visible only to package `bbb` or any child of `c1`. So, `c.a = 60;` is `CompileTimeError`, because `c1.a` is not visible from the `bbb` package and `c4` does not extends `c1`.

